  "texts": [
    "The first step of this review study was to conduct a bibliometric search in the Scopus database.",
    "The Scopus database was chosen because it is a widely known research database that provides broader journal coverage, interdisciplinary research outcomes, user-friendliness, and conven-ience as compared to other available databases such as Science Direct and Web of Science (Chadegani et al., 2013).",
    "To address the aforementioned research questions, some major key-words, such as \"artificial intelligence\", \"cloud computing\" and \"construction industry\" were used as search terms in Scopus to retrieve bibliographic records related to published articles in the field of AI-in-CC-in-CI.",
    "All keywords used in the Scopus search are shown in Table 3.",
    "Lit-erature search was conducted using search keywords in the \"title, abstract, and keywords\" sec-tion, with no date range limitations (up to February 4, 2023), resulting in a comprehensive da-taset of 669 articles."
